        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3058147911" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17656712519829705040">A look at how spices were viewed and used throughout recorded history, this book is quite comprehensive. It is interesting to see that spices had detractors as well as those who touted their virtues and the reasoning behind those disparate trains of thought. Delving into the medicinal uses to which people put them was amazing; some of the ways they were used and what they were supposed to cure were nothing short of astounding when viewed from today&apos;s vantage point. No matter how these condiments</span>
  <span id="freeText17656712519829705040" style="display:none">A look at how spices were viewed and used throughout recorded history, this book is quite comprehensive. It is interesting to see that spices had detractors as well as those who touted their virtues and the reasoning behind those disparate trains of thought. Delving into the medicinal uses to which people put them was amazing; some of the ways they were used and what they were supposed to cure were nothing short of astounding when viewed from today's vantage point. No matter how these condiments were used and, notwithstanding the naysayers, spices held enough mystique and panache for many to risk life and limb in their procurement in ages past. Today they may be commonplace and readily accessible but, as mentioned in this book - when something is taboo or hard to come by it is sought after all the more.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17656712519829705040" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
