        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3936632788" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5323916892712425083">Interesting look at spices from a European perspective. The desire for spices, not gold, inspired the age of exploration. Yet from the book, you get the impression that the primary cause of their allure was mystery, not flavor. Spices were valued less for what they did than for the fact that few people knew where they came from. Once they were no longer mysterious and hard to get, they became common place. The author probably didn&apos;t need 300 pages to say that.<br/>Still, it did make curious as to the</span>
  <span id="freeText5323916892712425083" style="display:none">Interesting look at spices from a European perspective. The desire for spices, not gold, inspired the age of exploration. Yet from the book, you get the impression that the primary cause of their allure was mystery, not flavor. Spices were valued less for what they did than for the fact that few people knew where they came from. Once they were no longer mysterious and hard to get, they became common place. The author probably didn't need 300 pages to say that.<br />Still, it did make curious as to the actual composition of medieval black pepper sauce.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5323916892712425083" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
